  Yes, you are using the `*` operator incorrectly. Here is a corrected version of your code:
```hs
factorial :: Int -> Integer
factorial n = case (n <= 0) of {
    _ -> -1
} else if (n == 1 || n == 0) then n else n * factorial (n-1) + factorial (n-2);
```
Note that this definition also allows for negative numbers as input. In particular, the function will return zero if given any number below one and will evaluate to infinity otherwise.</s>

