3) Availability - provide timely access to critical data when needed; 4) Authentication - verify identity of users accessing sensitive resources; 5) Access Control - control who has permission to access certain resources; 6) Accounting and Auditing – monitor activity for suspicious behavior; 7) Security Awareness – educate staff on security measures to help prevent breaches.</s>

