2. Opportunities for students to practice language skills through interactive activities, group work, or independent assignments; 
3. Strategies to help students acquire new vocabulary and grammatical concepts;
4. Activities focused on developing reading comprehension and fluency;
5. Instruction that is culturally relevant, taking into account the background and experiences of learners from different cultural contexts; and finally,
