- Soil management - using mulching or composting to retain moisture in soils and prevent erosion; 
- Lighting design - incorporating light sources into landscapes can enhance visual appeal and provide safety at night; 
- Structures & materials - selecting appropriate building materials and structures that complement the landscape; 
- Maintenance plans - planning for routine maintenance activities necessary to keep the space looking good over time. 
In addition, there are specific techniques used by landscape architects including planting schemes, grading, drainage systems, irrigation systems, stormwater control measures, and more. These are all designed with the goals of creating attractive outdoor environments while protecting and preserving existing resources and ecosystems.</s>

