- Sustainability - Designing with consideration for resource conservation, water efficiency, energy savings, etc.;
- Site analysis – Assessment of site conditions including climate, soil type, hydrology, geology, vegetation, topography;
- Topographical surveys – Measuring elevations, slopes, contours, drainage patterns, etc.;
- Master plans – Comprehensive plans for large scale projects or developments;
- Zoning regulations – Compliance with zoning codes governing development, setback requirements, building height limits, etc.; 
- Planting design – Selection of plants based on their suitability for specific environments, creating harmonious relationships between plant species;
- Water features – Planning of streams, ponds, fountains;
- Lighting design – Creating attractive nighttime ambiance using light sources like LED lights, torches, lamps, etc.;
